The paper deals with video understanding and temporal action detection, which are primarily computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a graph convolutional network (GCN) model, which involves learning from data and making predictions, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves multimedia analysis and retrieval, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with sub-graph localization, which involves searching for relevant information, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) a possible sub-category as well.
